args: (Pain sears my flesh like spreading fire...)
(This wound stands as proof of my\nbrother's victory.)
(He and I have been completely unalike\nsince we were but mewling babes.)
(I am fundamentally unable to\nunderstand the way he thinks and acts.)
(I thought him soft. He burdens himself\nwith the welfare of others. Relies on them.\nI believed it was the pinnacle of stupidity.)
(And yet who should emerge victorious\nfrom our bitter struggle? Not I, but him.)
(In victory lies verity.\nWhich means I must acknowledge that\n{player_name} was right.)
But I will not give in.\nI will not submit to draconic tyranny!
(Defeated or not, my objective remains\nthe same. Whatever method I must resort\nto, I WILL dismantle their reign.)
Whoops! Zigged when I should've zagged!
Wait! We're not up to no good, promise!
I am not sure this particular entrance\nlends you much credibility.
Prince Leonidas! Who are these people?!
Welp. So much for diplomacy.\nTake a nap, fella.
Don't worry. He's not dead—just taking\na little snooze. I got him with a special\ntranquilizer caster of mine.
That was close... He just grazed us.
But hey, where'd he get that caster? They\nshouldn't be widespread in this era.
＂This era,＂ you say? Who ARE you?\nFrom whence do you come?
Tell me your aims, your origins; all of it.\nOr I assure you my next shot will not miss\nits mark.
*whistle* Guy's covered in wounds,\nbut he's got spunk to spare, huh?
Spilling suits me just fine. You'll want\nto sit down for this one, though.
I'll tell you about the true history we\nsaw...down to the very last detail.
Maaan, what a night.\nTalk about a heart-pounding run-in!

And yet you didn't think to ask your
passenger if he was prone to
arrhythmia. Your reckless driving
got us into quite a serious mess.
You'll never understand the need for\nspeed, Mordecai. NEED. FOR. SPEED!
Focus on the board.\nMy turn is over. You're up.
Yeah, yeah. Now, take a look.\nThat move you called ＂reckless＂ is slowly\nbut surely getting me somewhere.
I've spread across the board.\nThe real game starts now.
Just like what we did that night,\nthese sorts of crazy plans can be\nsurprisingly effective.
You are a fool, and your heedlessness\nwill be your ruin one day.
D'awww, are you worried about me?\nDon't worry. It'll be fine.
For better or worse, I have the\nHolywyrm Elysium backing me up.
